We have studied 19 types of nanoclusters and some rel-
evant magic formulas for the number of atoms, bonds,
coordination numbers, and topological indices. These
include the fcc, bcc, hcp, the Platonic solids, diamond
cubic, simple cubic, and decahedral clusters. The majority
of these results are more detailed than previously deter-
mined, and a large number are enumerated for the first
time. Agrand goal of materials-related research is the cor-
